{{also|small-potatoes}}
==English==

===Etymology===
A specialization of a sense of {{m|en|potato}} meaning a thing of little value, and a comment on the low value of a small potato in particular, appearing in its modern form in North America in the mid-19th century (see 1855 quotation).

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|En-au-small potatoes.ogg|a=AU}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|p}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} One or more persons or things of relatively little [[consequence]], [[importance]], or [[value]].
#: {{ux|en|My paycheck is '''small potatoes''' compared to hers.}}
#: {{ux|en|He no longer works for individuals, since they are '''small potatoes''' compared to his corporate clients.}}
